<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-282-356  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 282 356.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  May 15 1989 v6 n19 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>X Windows software converts Commodore PC into X terminal. (GfxBaseInc.'s X11 software package) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   GfxBase Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   X11 (Computer program) (product introduction)Commodore Amiga (Microcomputer).andO;Topic:     Terminal EmulationX Windows (Standard)Software PackagesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>X Windows Software Converts Commodore PC into X TerminalandM;MILPITAS, Calif.andP;  -- Want to access X windows from your very own CommodoreAmiga PC at home?andP;  GfxBase has announced a release of the X11 X windowssystem that runs on the Amiga PC, which in its most inexpensive version ischeaper than a low-end X terminal.andM;&quot;Amiga is the lowest-cost PC that you can get that will support a version ofX windows,&quot; said Dale Luck, president of GfxBase.andM;Luck said there's plenty of &quot;untapped potential&quot; for Amiga users who choosethis option.andM;&quot;The Amiga has built-in graphics, and, although the current server doesn'tsupport color, it will in the future, and custom hardware makes the graphicsquick, even though it's a 68000 machine,&quot; he explained.andM;&quot;A lot of sites are using Amiga as their primary video machine.andP;  It providesthe ability to mix video and overlay with graphics--and now you can use Xdisplays and overlay live video,&quot; he said.andM;Luck added that the Amiga is faster than a Sun-3/50.andM;The Amiga X11 software runs TCP/IP over Ethernet for connections to othermachines and has a shared-memory message-passing scheme for localconnections, officials said.andM;Eventually, the Amiga X11 will have the capability of supporting DECnetrunning over serial lines to TSSnet, Luck said.andM;The native windowing system for Amiga coexists with X11, and users can splitthe Amiga display into multiple bit maps with different resolutions and colormaps, the officials said.andM;&quot;You can split the display up into multiple displays, each with its ownpalette, and with X as another virtual device in the Amiga workbenchdisplay,&quot; Luck said.&quot;andM;Amiga's X windows system works with VAXes and with Sun, Apollo andHewlett-Packard workstations.andP;  The product is available now.andM;Xlib and Xt libraries will be included later this year, according toofficials.andM;X11 for the Amiga is priced at $395; with the inclusion of a three-buttonmouse, the price is $475.andP;  The Ethernet board is priced at $1,339, and anAmiga with the minimum memory requirement of 1MB for running X11 is $950,Luck said.andM;GfxBase Inc. is located at 1881 Ellwell Drive, Milpitas, CA 95035, (408)262-1469.andO;</TEXT></DOC>